<text>
	<body>
		<pb n="468"/>
                <div>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.1.</head> <l>In nomine Domini dicam, vos audite,</l>
                            <l>Vestro bono proferam &lt;vobis&gt; quicquid scite;</l>
                            <l>Primo detis veniam lingue non polite,</l>
                            <l>Gerarde cum sotiis, doctor redimite. </l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.2.</head> <l n="5">Duo vobis referampro vestri honore:</l>
                            <l>Primo de Ambrosioloquar pre dolore,</l>
                            <l>De vestro dulcissimodefuncto pastore,</l>
                            <l>Et secundo breviterde novo doctore. </l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.3.</head> <l>Mea tristis animaest usque ad mortem,</l>
                            <l n="10">Orphanam Ambrosividens hanc cohortem:</l>
                            <l>Dolorosam ideo,heu, heu, tristem sortem!</l>
                            <l>Omnis mende nocuitmors virum exortem. </l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.4.</head> <l>Modo est Bononia bona viduata,</l>
                            <l>Patrono grammatice tota minorata:</l>
                            <l n="15">Totus mundus conqueri potest cur orbata,</l>
                            <l>Et cur est Ambrosio vita iam sublata. </l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.5.</head> <l>Tedet meam animam modo mee vite,</l>
                            <l>In amaritudine loquar, nec florite:</l>
                            <l>O vos, omnes homines, auditum venite,</l>
                            <l n="20">Quid mors nobis triverit, &lt;dicam nunc&gt;, audite.</l>
                    </lg>
                    <pb n="469"/>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.6.</head> <l>O lamma sabactani, Hely, quid fecisti?</l>
                            <l>Luminare maximum tu cur extinxisti,</l>
                            <l>Et fontem grammatice vivum destruxisti ?</l>
                            <l>Cur tam cito, Domine, solem abstulisti? .</l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.7.</head> <l n="25">Phebus inter sidera nunc est obscuratus,</l>
                            <l>Leo inter bestias nunc est superatus,</l>
                            <l>Inter aves aquila perdidit volatus:</l>
                            <l>Immo supra sidera est doctor prelatus. .</l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.8.</head> <l>Magdalena lacrimans, Petre preelecte,</l>
                            <l n="30">Iacob, [[et]] Rachel, plangite, gens unius secte,</l>
                            <l>O Ioseph, o Ionatha. Ambrosi dilecte,</l>
                            <l>Pro te dolens conqueror et lamentor recte. .</l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.9.</head> <l>Nostri vera capitis decidit corona,</l>
                            <l>Immo mundi corruit miranda persona,</l>
                            <l n="35">Que prebebat omnibus tot et tanta dona,</l>
                            <l>Ex omni scientia quod undabat dona. .</l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.10.</head> <l>Dolens pro Ambrosio plorat Priscianus,</l>
                            <l>Donatus, Virgilius, Prosper et Lucanus,</l>
                            <l>Cato et Boetius Statius, Alanus,</l>
                            <l n="40">Seneca, Ovidius, Plato, Claudianus. .</l>
                    </lg>
                    <pb n="470"/>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.11.</head> <l>Post plorat Oratius, Nova Poetria,</l>
                            <l>Herricetus , Pamphilus, Facetus, Tobia,</l>
                            <l>Idemque Ugutio et liber Papia.</l>
                            <l>Plangit Astrolabius et philosophia. .</l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.12.</head> <l n="45">Maris stella, Persius plorat virginalis,</l>
                            <l>Arator, Terentius atque Iuvenalis,</l>
                            <l>Alexander, Tullius, plorat Marcialis,</l>
                            <l>Grecismus, Sedulius atque Doctrinalis, .</l>
                    </lg>
                    <pb n="471"/>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.13.</head> <l>Theodolus [ . . . ] et Maximianus,</l>
                            <l n="50">Esopus, Salustius atque Avianus,</l>
                            <l>Et Doctrina rudium atque Ulpianus,</l>
                            <l>Euclides, Evendeunt atque Alphraganus, .</l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.14.</head> <l>Aly, Aristotiles, Tolomeus plenus,</l>
                            <l>Constantinus, Ypocras, Rasis, Abicenus,</l>
                            <l n="55">Alcidus, Avicebron, et post Galienus,</l>
                            <l>Algazel, Avenroys, plorat Damascenus, .</l>
                    </lg>
                    <pb n="472"/>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.15.</head> <l>Plorant generaliter nunc omnes artiste,</l>
                            <l>Naturales medici, morales sophiste,</l>
                            <l>Et sacri theologi et omnes iuriste:</l>
                            <l n="60">Conquerantur etiam omnes alchimiste. .</l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.16.</head> <l>Nunc plangat Ambrosium sua Margarita,</l>
                            <l>Auctorum opuscula fleant infinita,</l>
                            <l>Libri fleant singuli et librorum scita</l>
                            <l>Ambrosii mortua pro lingua mellita. .</l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.17.</head> <l n="65">Sed nil iuvat plangere, ergo consolemur:</l>
                            <l>Istud scimus firmiter, quod nos moriemur,</l>
                            <l>Cunctis modis igitur Deo famulemur,</l>
                            <l>Ut in summa gloria simul gloriemur. .</l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.18.</head> <l>Debemusque plurimis causis consolari:</l>
                            <l n="70">Non potest Ambrosius plus recuperari;</l>
                            <l>Ita Deo placuit, debet conlaudari,</l>
                            <l>Et quod nobis expeditdecet comparari. .</l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.19.</head> <l>Dimittamus mortuos cum mortuis esse,</l>
                            <l>Vivi cum viventibus letemur expresse,</l>
                            <l n="75">Faciamus attamen quod est plus necesse,</l>
                            <l>Omittendo quilibet quod potest obesse. .</l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.20.</head> <l>Sotii karissimi, Modo audiatis,</l>
                            <l>Optimum consilium Nunc suscipiatis:</l>
                            <l>Magistro continue Gyrhardo credatis,</l>
                            <l n="80">Illi sitis subditi, Illum timeatis. .</l>
                    </lg>
                    <pb n="473"/>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.21.</head> <l>Magister Ambrosius ita ordinavit,</l>
                            <l>Suas scolas libere Gyrhaldo donavit,</l>
                            <l>Vobis utilissimum quod esse putavit;</l>
                            <l>Est et erit, siquidem hec Deus mandavit. .</l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.22.</head> <l n="85">Gerardi sub ferula&lt;misit&gt; militare,</l>
                            <l>Et si forsan queritis, dico vobis quare;</l>
                            <l>Breviter respondeo: quod est citra mare</l>
                            <l>Pre cunctis grammaticis maius luminare; .</l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.23.</head> <l>Successit grammatico cunctis meliori,</l>
                            <l n="90">Successit scientie, successit honori,</l>
                            <l>Et modis et gestibus eius et amori:</l>
                            <l>Vos Girardo igitur subsitis doctori. .</l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.24.</head> <l>Gyrardus in omnibus vos illuminabit,</l>
                            <l>In tota grammatica vos clarificabit,</l>
                            <l n="95">Naturam grammatice novit et monstrabit,</l>
                            <l>Vobis necessaria cuncta propinabit. .</l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.25.</head> <l>Salvetur societas istic omni hora,</l>
                            <l>Gaudeat societas ista quam decora,</l>
                            <l>Cuius doctor providus surgens cum aurora</l>
                            <l n="100">[…..] placida † dulcora † .</l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                            <head>.26.</head> <l>Et[ . . . amen].</l>
                            <l>Assit vobis omnibus [ . . . ] iuv[amen],</l>
                            <l>Salus, vita, gaudium dicam et sol[amen]:</l>
                            <l>Vestrum clamet quilibet: fiat, fiat, [amen]. .</l>
                    </lg>
            </div>
